<tr id="L293"><td><a href="#L293">293</a></td><td>JETREL:  Yes, exactly! Neelix saw it. It was an amalgamation of randomly fused organic material. Bits and pieces of previously vaporised biomatter.</td></tr>

<tr id="L294"><td><a href="#L294">294</a></td><td>NEELIX:  But, but, if the biomatter in the cloud is so random, so jumbled, how could you reconstruct something whole?</td></tr>

<tr id="L295"><td><a href="#L295">295</a></td><td>JETREL:  I used medical records to identify the genetic coding of a specific victim, a test case if you will. Once we input his DNA sequence, then we can isolate his atomic fragments with your targeting scanners, and then rematerialise him.</td></tr>

<tr id="L296"><td><a href="#L296">296</a></td><td>NEELIX:  What if he's right?</td></tr>

<tr id="L297"><td><a href="#L297">297</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Captain, Doctor Jetrel is proposing the reconstruction and re-animation of a remarkable complex set of biosystems from billions of subatomic particles.</td></tr>

<tr id="L298"><td><a href="#L298">298</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  I'm afraid I have to agree. It all sounds very implausible.</td></tr>

<tr id="L299"><td><a href="#L299">299</a></td><td>JETREL:  You sound exactly like my country. I asked them for more funds to continue my research to help the victims of Rinax, because I wanted the world to know I'm not a monster. My theories can be used to heal, as well as to destroy. But they refused me, called me a Talaxian sympathiser, and exiled me.</td></tr>

<tr id="L300"><td><a href="#L300">300</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Does Neelix really have metremia, or was that just a pretext for getting us to come to Rinax.</td></tr>

<tr id="L301"><td><a href="#L301">301</a></td><td>JETREL:  It was just a pretext, Captain. You do not have metremia, Neelix. You are not going to die.</td></tr>

<tr id="L302"><td><a href="#L302">302</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Why didn't you just tell us the truth in the first place?</td></tr>

<tr id="L303"><td><a href="#L303">303</a></td><td>JETREL:  Your Captain is an accomplished scientist. She doubts my theories. My own government did too. I just could not risk being not believed again. But, Captain, it will work.</td></tr>

<tr id="L304"><td><a href="#L304">304</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Captain, if there's any chance he can do it, you've got to let him try.</td></tr>

<tr id="L305"><td><a href="#L305">305</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Neelix, there are just too many variables.</td></tr>

<tr id="L306"><td><a href="#L306">306</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Please, Captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L307"><td><a href="#L307">307</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Lieutenant Tuvok, activate the emergency containment field around the transporter pad.</td></tr>

<tr id="L308"><td><a href="#L308">308</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Aye, Captain. Emergency containment field activated.</td></tr>

<tr id="L309"><td><a href="#L309">309</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  We'll have to re-target scanners to the widest possible confinement beam. It's our only hope of achieving bond cohesion with such broadly scattered fragments.</td></tr>

<tr id="L310"><td><a href="#L310">310</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Re-targeting scanners to wide beam.</td></tr>

<tr id="L311"><td><a href="#L311">311</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Energise. Phase transition coils to maximum.</td></tr>

<tr id="L312"><td><a href="#L312">312</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Aye, Captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L313"><td><a href="#L313">313</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: A vaguely humanoid shape begins to appear.</td></tr>

<tr id="L314"><td><a href="#L314">314</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Is the biogenic field operational?</td></tr>

<tr id="L315"><td><a href="#L315">315</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Affirmative.</td></tr>

<tr id="L316"><td><a href="#L316">316</a></td><td>NEELIX:  It's incredible.</td></tr>

<tr id="L317"><td><a href="#L317">317</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Atomic cohesion has dropped to forty nine percent, Captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L318"><td><a href="#L318">318</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Pattern buffers to maximum power.</td></tr>

<tr id="L319"><td><a href="#L319">319</a></td><td>TUVOK:  They are already at one hundred percent.</td></tr>

<tr id="L320"><td><a href="#L320">320</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Take them to one twenty, Lieutenant.</td></tr>

<tr id="L321"><td><a href="#L321">321</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: The figure starts to writhe.</td></tr>

<tr id="L322"><td><a href="#L322">322</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Pattern buffers to one hundred and twenty percent of rated maximum.</td></tr>

<tr id="L323"><td><a href="#L323">323</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  We're losing him.</td></tr>

<tr id="L324"><td><a href="#L324">324</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Atomic cohesion to thirty nine percent. Twenty two percent. Fourteen percent. His pattern is degrading rapidly.</td></tr>

<tr id="L325"><td><a href="#L325">325</a></td><td>JETREL:  You must increase the power to the pattern buffers, Captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L326"><td><a href="#L326">326</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  We've got to stimulate cohesion. Is there anyway to augment the biogenic field?</td></tr>

<tr id="L327"><td><a href="#L327">327</a></td><td>TUVOK:  The degree of fragmentation is simply too great. It will not work. We are overloading the system.</td></tr>

<tr id="L328"><td><a href="#L328">328</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: The figure dissipates.</td></tr>

<tr id="L329"><td><a href="#L329">329</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Shut it down, Mister Tuvok.</td></tr>

<tr id="L330"><td><a href="#L330">330</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Jetrel collapses.</td></tr>

<tr id="L331"><td><a href="#L331">331</a></td><td>SOMEONE: Captain's log, stardate 48840.5. Doctor Jetrel's metremia is now in it's final stage. He's spending his remaining hours in Sickbay.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Sickbay</td></tr>
<tr id="L332"><td><a href="#L332">332</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: The dying man has a visitor.</td></tr>

<tr id="L333"><td><a href="#L333">333</a></td><td>JETREL:  Neelix. I suppose you think this is a fitting punishment for me.</td></tr>

<tr id="L334"><td><a href="#L334">334</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Maybe the Cascade was a punishment for all of us, for our hatred, our brutality. There's something I need to tell you. I tried to tell you before, but</td></tr>

<tr id="L335"><td><a href="#L335">335</a></td><td>JETREL:  What is it?</td></tr>

<tr id="L336"><td><a href="#L336">336</a></td><td>NEELIX:  I want to tell you that I forgive you.</td></tr>

